  "text": "In the frame of BRITESPACE project, we report a feasi bility study of a new type of IPDA lidar for space-borne remote sensing applications. The proposed system applies the PRSPC [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] technique and uses a high-gain, low noise DC-coupled Single Photon Avalanche Photodiode (SPAD). It also incorporates two high brightness semiconductor laser sources one for each sounding frequency, emitting near 1. 572 �. Preliminarily experimental results have proven its feasibility in terms of precision and linearity.",
